# Template for local secret values — copy to secrets.env (gitignored) and
# fill in real values there. Never commit secrets.env itself.
#
# Push its contents into GitHub's encrypted repo secrets with:
#   gh secret set --repo donverduyn/ha-pylontech-mqtt --env-file secrets.env
#
# UPDATE_PR_TOKEN: fine-grained PAT scoped to this repo only, with
# Contents: Read and write and Pull requests: Read and write. Used by
# .github/workflows/dependency-updates.yaml so PRs it opens are attributed
# to a real actor (not the default GITHUB_TOKEN) and therefore still
# trigger pull_request-based required checks (HACS Action / validate /
# tests-finished) — see that workflow's checkout step for why this matters.
UPDATE_PR_TOKEN=
